│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                          │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure in                          │
│ DomTreeUpdater::validateDeleteBB, which requires that a basic block      │
│ being deleted has no predecessors (pred_empty(DelBB)). In IPSCCP, we     │
│ mark dead blocks and attempt to delete them using DTU.deleteBB(DeadBB).  │
│ However, the pass only turns dead blocks into unreachable                │
│ (changeToUnreachable) and then removes non-feasible edges for executable │
│ blocks. It does not guarantee that all incoming edges to dead blocks are │
│ removed before calling deleteBB. As a result, DTU.deleteBB is invoked on │
│ blocks that still have predecessors, triggering the assertion.           │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                  │
│ The log shows:                                                           │
│ - Dead blocks identified: "BasicBlock Dead: loop ... exit" for           │
│ callee-like functions.                                                   │
│ - changeToUnreachable is applied to the first non-PHI instruction of     │
│ dead blocks.                                                             │
│ - Then removeNonFeasibleEdges runs and may rewrite some terminators but  │
│ focuses on feasible edges from analyzed blocks. It doesn't necessarily   │
│ remove all incoming edges into dead blocks.                              │
│ - Finally, DTU.deleteBB is called for each DeadBB in BlocksToErase       │
│ without checking pred_empty, which leads to the assertion:               │
│ validateDeleteBB's pred_empty check fails.                               │
│ This sequence matches the first transformation point and the backtrace   │
│ and aligns with the observed behavior that the block still has           │
│ predecessors at deletion time.                                           │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ IPSCCP's deletion logic assumes that, after changeToUnreachable and edge │
│ cleanup, the dead basic blocks will be isolated (no predecessors). This  │
│ is not always the case. SCCP solver's removeNonFeasibleEdges only        │
│ processes br/switch/indirectbr terminators for blocks that it decides to │
│ change and does so per-block; it does not globally ensure all preds are  │
│ removed for every dead block. Consequently, BlocksToErase may still have │
│ predecessors when DTU.deleteBB is called, violating DTU's precondition.  │
│ The assertion is correct; the pass is attempting an illegal deletion.    │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ Edit llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/SCCP.cpp around lines 249-252 to add a      │
│ pred_empty check before calling DTU.deleteBB. This keeps deletion safe   │
│ and defers the removal of such blocks to later cleanup passes if         │
│ predecessors remain.                                                     │
│                                                                          │
│ Current code:                                                            │
│   for (BasicBlock *DeadBB : BlocksToErase)                               │
│     if (!DeadBB->hasAddressTaken())                                      │
│       DTU.deleteBB(DeadBB);                                              │
│                                                                          │
│ Proposed change:                                                         │
│   for (BasicBlock *DeadBB : BlocksToErase) {                             │
│     if (DeadBB->hasAddressTaken())                                       │
│       continue;                                                          │
│     // Only delete blocks that are fully disconnected to respect DTU     │
│ preconditions.                                                           │
│     if (pred_empty(DeadBB))                                              │
│       DTU.deleteBB(DeadBB);                                              │
│     // Otherwise, keep them with an unreachable terminator; later passes │
│ will clean up.                                                           │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ This ensures we only call DTU.deleteBB when the block has no             │
│ predecessors, satisfying validateDeleteBB. It aligns with the intended   │
│ pipeline: mark dead, make unreachable, remove non-feasible edges where   │
│ possible, and only delete blocks when safe.                              │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The fix guards DTU.deleteBB with pred_empty to respect DomTreeUpdater's  │
│ invariants. This prevents the assertion and maintains correctness: dead  │
│ blocks are left with unreachable terminators when predecessors still     │
│ exist, allowing subsequent CFG simplification/DCE passes to safely       │
│ remove them once edges are gone. The change is minimal, localized, and   │
│ consistent with DTU's contract.                                          │
